Bill Gross, who runs the world's 
biggest bond fund at Pacific Investment Management Co., talks 
about global recession risk, fixed-income allocation in the 
current environment, developing-market equities and monetary 
policies of the Federal Reserve and European Central Bank.  Gross speaks with Lisa Murphy and Adam Johnson on Bloomberg
Television's "Street Smart." (Source: Bloomberg)  00:00 Rising recession risk in global economies
02:02 Investment strategy: safe sovereign assets
03:13 Investments below sovereign government debt
04:34 Sovereign debt of U.K., Germany, France
06:00 Economic recovery, debt rebalancing
06:56 Equities in developing markets
08:07 Monetary policies of the Fed and ECB  Running time 09:46
 